        <p> ___Twig_token_1___ in the sun, read, snorkeled and enjoyed the late summer feeling to the fullest. This time the water was particularly clear - and even a small swarm of barracudas showed up. A nice end to our time on the island. </p>
        <p> On the last evening we strolled to the Plaza del Duque Mall after dinner. Like the Siam Mall not quite our case - but the walk along the promenade was worth it. Light wind, the lights, a little sound of the sea in the background ... the perfect last evening moment. </p>
        <p> The last morning it was said: slowly saying goodbye. While Basti was already checking out, I spontaneously treated myself to an appointment in the nail studio. My nails were just so long and stable that it was finally worth it - and Basti's Christmas present from 2020 was also redeemed. Some things just need time. </p>
        <p> Our transfer bus was ready on time at 12:30 p.m. We had to wait at the airport because the switch was not yet open - but with the sun in the back you can sit out of something very relaxed. The plane was almost empty, just 94 people on board. Pure luxury: endless space. </p>

